          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              The regulatory stuff is something I'm struggling with  - the backup issues mostly. From what I can gather, most providers offer only a few weeks restore capability. What happens when someone accidentally deletes something and only finds out a few months later? Or if we need to perform an audit on someone's email from a few years ago?<br /><br />Balanced against that is an increasing number of new senior management who only seem to want iDevices, gmail, and Skype. Is Corporate IT devolving into just the provision of a big Internet pipe, wifi, and contracts with Cloud providers?

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
