              It's interesting to me how much people make out of the &quot;cloud&quot; thing. It's not the hardware that's the difference, it's who has control of your data and if they can provide the level of security your .org needs.<br /><br />Well managed infrastructure is almost infinitely scalable so it makes sense that eventually my compute/storage/communicate resources will be hosted by someone else. I expect that most companies will slowly cut off the lower levels of the software stack as IT evolved. There is little reason for me to keep a VMware guy on hand if I can trust Azure/Rackspace/whoever to fill that role. My business does not rely on VMware, it relies on the services IT can provide. I hate the thought of that eventually being someone in Accounts Payable who manages the IT budget but for SMB I think that will be the eventual outcome (from an infrastructure side, development will likely move closer to primary business roles - think Marketing people writing their own dashboards or Finance creating their own reporting).<br /><br />Might take another 100 years though.

              

              
              
